transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I just received a bill on my Amex for a shipment. I never ordered, I never signed up for a subscription.

Speaker 1: Okay, give me a second. I'm going to pull up your profile and get you help. All right, Jeffrey, can you just confirm your date of birth?

Speaker 2: 9-10-48.

Speaker 1: Thank you so much. Is your VIP status customer? Oh, I see you on, they put you on automatic refills on a monthly basis.

Speaker 2: Give me a second. I'm going to cancel that out for you.

Speaker 1: All right, perfect. Jeffrey, I was able to cancel out that refill.

Speaker 2: So you'll be seeing $63.95 back on your credit card in about five business days or less.

Speaker 1: And then how is the medication working out for you?

Speaker 2: I haven't tried it yet.

Speaker 1: Oh, okay. Yeah, so with your VIP status, you don't have to have your refills on a monthly basis.

Speaker 2: What a lot of people like to do is just go ahead and pause that for six months.

Speaker 1: That way it keeps your prescription active and just allows you to call in anytime you need a refill. And it keeps your price rate locked in.

Speaker 2: So prices go up, yours stays the same.

Speaker 1: I could pause that for you until July 31st.

Speaker 2: That's okay, if they'll notify me in advance.

Speaker 1: No, that's the only thing, they don't.

Speaker 2: All right, then I don't want to freeze it, no.

Speaker 1: All right, no problem.

Speaker 2: I went ahead and canceled you out. You're all set.

Speaker 1: Very good. Thanks very much.

Speaker 2: No problem. Have a great evening. Bye.
